-- Network Rail Said to Hire Banks for Three-Year Bonds in Pounds
-- B y   H a n n a h   B e n j a m i n
-- 2012-01-03T14:39:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/network-rail-said-to-hire-banks-for-three-year-bonds-in-pounds.html
Network Rail Infrastructure Finance
Plc is selling three-year bonds in pounds, according to a banker
involved in the transaction.  Deutsche Bank AG,  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) , Royal Bank of Scotland
Group Plc and UBS AG are managing the deal, the banker said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
